{"word":"πλουτέω","slug":"πλουτέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πλουτέω</b></el> <el>(πλουτέω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>πλοῦτος</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to be rich, wealthy</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic; <el>πλ. ἀπὸ τῶν κοινῶν</el> <i>to be rich</i> from the public purse, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <i>to be rich in</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> rei, <el>πλ. ἐμπύροισιν</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>4. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>πλ. πλοῦτον</el> <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}